Expense Operating Investment Asset Consultant Fees Amount

Record the expense for fees paid/payable to asset consultants engaged by the trustees, in relation to the management of the superannuation entity's investment portfolios. Include fees paid to independent third parties as well as related entities of the superannuation entity.
Include all expenses which are associated with the generation of income on the investment portfolio of the entity. Do not include expenses of an administrative or operating nature. Important! Do not net fee related income rebates off against investment expenses. Commissions or deductions should be shown on a gross basis here. For example, where there is a separately identifiable charge to the entity, fees charged by the asset consultants should not be netted against investment income.
Expense Operating Investment Custodian Fees Amount
Report the expense of the superannuation entity that was incurred in relation to custodial services rendered to the entity.
A custodian is an entity that holds title of the assets on behalf of the superannuation entity, but where the powers of investment management remain with the Trustee.
Expense Operating Investment Management And Asset Consultant Fees Amount

Record the amount of fee expense of the superannuation entity that relates to the management of the superannuation entity's investment portfolios. Include fees paid to investment managers, including independent third parties as well as related entities of the superannuation entity. Include asset consultant fees at this item.
Include all expenses which are associated with the generation of income on the investment portfolio of the entity. Do not include expenses of an administrative or operating nature. Important! Do not net the following revenue items off against investment expenses: * fee related income rebates off against investment expenses; or * rebates provided by investment managers (often in the form of extra units when investment performance does not meet targets). Commissions or deductions should be shown on a gross basis here. For example, where there is a separately identifiable charge to the entity, fees charged by the investment manager should not be netted against investment income.

Include all expenses which are associated with the generation of income on the investment portfolio of the entity. Do not include expenses of an administrative or operating nature. Important! Do not net the following revenue items off against investment expenses: * fee related income rebates off against investment expenses; or * rebates provided by investment managers (often in the form of extra units when investment performance does not meet targets). Commissions or deductions should be shown on a gross basis here. For example, where there is a separately identifiable charge to the entity, fees charged by the investment manager should not be netted against investment income.

Income Sale Of Goods Not Produced By Business Amount
The amount received when a sale of goods that are not assembled, grown or manufactured by a business is made. Goods are defined as commodities that satisfy human needs.

Income Sale Of Goods And Services Balancing Items Amount

This element is the balancing item in a list of "Income.Sales Of Goods And Services" items. It is the difference between "Income.Sales Of Goods And Services.Whole.Amount" and the separately disclosed items in the list.
Income Sale Of Goods And Services Excluding Rent Leasing Hiring And Royalties Amount

The amount received when sale of a good or service is made.
Goods are defined as commodities that satisfy human needs. Services are defined as activities or benefits that one party can offer to another, that are intangible and do not result in the transfer of ownership of any physical object.
The amount reported excludes rent, leasing and hiring income and royalties.
Income Sale Of Goods And Services Includes Rent Leasing Hiring And Royalties Amount

The amount received when sale of a good or service is made.
Goods are defined as commodities that satisfy human needs. Services are defined as activities or benefits that one party can offer to another, that are intangible and do not result in the transfer of ownership of any physical object.
The amount reported includes rent, leasing and hiring income and royalties.
Income Sale Of Goods And Services Reason For Difference Description

Income from the sales of goods and services is defined as the sum received when sale of a good or service is made.
Goods are defined as commodities that satisfy human needs. Services are defined as activities or benefits that one party can offer to another, that are intangible and do not result in the transfer of ownership of any physical object.
The reason for the difference between reporting periods is the cause or events that have resulted in a variation of greater than 10 percent from the value reported in the previous reporting period.
Income Sale Of Goods And Services Tax Included Indicator
This indicates whether the total sales figure includes GST or not.
Income Sale Of Goods And Services Whole Amount
If you use the calculation sheet method, this figure less any GST free or input tax sales divided by 11 will be the clients GST liability.
This represents the total sales amount for the period against which the GST payable is calculated.

Profit Or Loss Continuing Operations Before Tax Reason For Difference Description

Profit or loss is defined as the residual amount that remains after expenses (including capital maintenance adjustments, where appropriate) have been deducted from income. The reason for the difference between reporting periods is the cause or events that have resulted in reported profit or loss varying by greater than 10 percent from the value reported in the previous reporting period.

Profit or loss is the residual amount that remains after expenses (including capital maintenance adjustments, where appropriate) have been deducted from income.
Reported operating profit or loss before tax is defined as the profit or loss reported by a reporting party as a result of its principal trading activity before the application of income tax. This amount is derived by deducting operating expenses from operating income prior to the application of income tax.
Profit Or Loss Continuing Operations Before Tax Revised Amount

Profit Or Loss Foreign Exchange Derivatives Amount

Report any realised/unrealised foreign exchange gains/losses relating to the currency translation/conversion of derivative contracts. Such contracts may be held in relation to the underlying investment portfolios (e.g. as hedges of the interest rate or equity investment portfolios) or as outright position taking to alter the asset allocation strategy. Only report the gain/loss that is attributable to movements in the currency in which the derivative contract is denominated, relative to the AUD.
Profit Or Loss Foreign Exchange Physical Amount

Report any realised/unrealised foreign exchange gains/losses relating to the translation/conversion of all investments of the entity (except derivatives) which are denominated in a currency other than the Australian dollar (AUD). Only report the gain/loss that is attributable to movements in the currency in which investments are denominated, relative to the AUD.
Profit Or Loss Foreign Exchange Total Amount

Report any realised/unrealised foreign exchange gains/losses relating to the translation/conversion of all investments of the entity which are denominated in a currency other than the Australian dollar (AUD). Only report the gain/loss that is attributable to movements in the currency in which investments are denominated, relative to the AUD.

Profit Or Loss Investment Deposits Placements Loans Securities Amount

Report realised gains/losses associated with the entity's holdings of deposits, placements, loans and debt securities. Exclude * Gains and losses associated with the investment in cash management trusts; and * Gains/losses on interest rate related derivative financial instruments.
Realised gains/losses Where the entity disposed of an asset during the reporting period, the value of the gain or loss from the disposal is to be reported. If an asset has not been disposed of during the annual reporting period, then any gains or losses are unrealised. Only include the movement in the market value of the asset, do not include the movement in the value of the currency relative to the Australian dollar if the asset is denominated in a currency other than the Australian dollar.
Profit Or Loss Investment Derivatives Amount

Report realised gains/losses attributable to the movement in net market value of the entity's derivative exposures. Exclude Unrealised or realised gains/losses relating to the currency translation of foreign currency derivative contracts.
Realised gains/losses Where the entity disposed of an asset during the reporting period, the value of the gain or loss from the disposal is to be reported. If an asset has not been disposed of during the annual reporting period, then any gains or losses are unrealised. Only include the movement in the market value of the asset, do not include the movement in the value of the currency relative to the Australian dollar if the asset is denominated in a currency other than the Australian dollar.
Profit Or Loss Investment Equity And Unit Trusts Listed Amount

This includes realised gains/losses on the entity's investment in equity securities and unit trusts that are listed on recognised stock exchanges (e.g. The Australian Securities Exchange). Exclude * Gains/losses on equity related derivative contracts; and * Gains/losses on direct investments in Pooled Super Trusts.
Realised gains/losses Where the entity disposed of an asset during the reporting period, the value of the gain or loss from the disposal is to be reported. If an asset has not been disposed of during the annual reporting period, then any gains or losses are unrealised. Only include the movement in the market value of the asset, do not include the movement in the value of the currency relative to the Australian dollar if the asset is denominated in a currency other than the Australian dollar.
Profit Or Loss Investment Equity And Unit Trusts Unlisted And Ventures Amount

This includes realised gains/losses on the entity's investment in equity securities and unit trusts that are not listed on recognised stock exchanges (e.g. The Australian Securities Exchange). Exclude * Gains/losses on equity related derivative contracts; and * Gains/losses on direct investments in Pooled Super Trusts.
Realised gains/losses Where the entity disposed of an asset during the reporting period, the value of the gain or loss from the disposal is to be reported. If an asset has not been disposed of during the annual reporting period, then any gains or losses are unrealised. Only include the movement in the market value of the asset, do not include the movement in the value of the currency relative to the Australian dollar if the asset is denominated in a currency other than the Australian dollar.
Profit Or Loss Investment Individually Managed Mandates Amount
